<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-19-0457 </DOCNO><TEXT>Facts and figures about the uranium supply and demand are presented. Theuranium market is complex and fluctuates widely although, in generalterms, uranium demand is a function of installed nuclear generating capacity,which in turn depends on overall electricity demand and utilities' decisionsabout the means of generation. These factors are discussed. Demand isexpected to increase gradually but steadily over the following decadeand beyond. However, although the total supplies of uranium are ampleto meet the foreseen demand, the potential exists for significant localand regional disruption of both supply and demand.</TEXT></DOC>